<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.207557>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Branchinecta mediospinosa n. sp. Types A) Male, left side of head anterior view, upper arrow indicates pulvillus, lower arrow indicates medial projection. B) Female, anterior view. C) Male second antenna distal antennomere apex, apical view. D) Same, medial view. E) Same, posterior view. F) Male left gonopod, everted, ventrolateral view. G) Female right lateral view, bracket indicates thoracic lobes. Scale bar represents 1 mm for A and B, 0.5 mm for C, D, E, 0.25 mm for F, and 2 mm for G." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/207557/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

